title: Charles Christopher Parry
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
description: Charles Christopher Parry, botanist and physician, lived in Davenport, Iowa. In 1849 he was appointed botanist to the United States-Mexican boundary survey and worked in this capacity for three years. For the rest of his life, Parry spent his summers in botanical expeditions in the western United States.

title: Charles C. Parry field notebook no. 2: botany & geology, 1849-1850
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
creator: Parry, C. C. (Charles Christopher), 1823-1890
description: Field notes on the botany, geography, and climate of Southern California. Includes detailed botanical descriptions of several species of plants.
subject: Botany;Geography;Scientific expeditions;Cactus;Weather;Imperialism

title: Charles C. Parry field notebook, expedition to the Gila, September 1849-February 1850
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
creator: Parry, C. C. (Charles Christopher), 1823-1890
description: Field notes and observations from the Expedition to the Gila, September-December 1849. Includes a "sick report", description of food cultivated and gathered by the Yuma people at North Gila, thermometer readings and weather reports, barometric observations, sketches, and hand-drawn maps.
